 •  Involve for development, establish, implement and maintain Departmental policy, procedures and systems, and monitor the adherence of these procedures within company and its Business Partners; 
 •  Involve for development and maintain departmental plans that are pro-active in planning to ensure that the day-to-day operational needs are met while counterbalancing the strict Project and control requirements in line with Indonesian or better standards; 
 •  Involve in develop and enforce sound and practical standard operational and task procedures, which fit the global standards while ensuring a continually improving approach on Projects and control the facilities. 
 •  Assist sets goals and coordinates the activities of the department reports in the field, workshop and various administrative office ensure consistent and quality scheduled maintenance and unscheduled maintenance are accomplished with minimal disruption to the operation; 
 •  Involve in development and enforce sound and practical standard operational and task procedures, which fit the global standards while ensuring a continually improving approach to a better delivery of support and operational services; 
 •  Ensure that international-quality office and support infrastructure facilities are available which meet the needs of the company workforce and its Business Partners; 

<b> What skills and experience do you need?</b> 
 •  Minimum Bachelor Degree in <b>Electrical Engineering</b> (for LEAD QA/ QC ELECTRIC &amp; INSTRUMENTATION 
 •  Has 12 years’ experience industry preferable have exposure in Mill Expansion Processing Plant / EPC Industry. 
 •  Must have had 5 years’ experience in similar role as Lead/ Senior Engineer Quality Control/ Quality Assurance for each of discipline. 
 •  Have substantial experience in the Domestic, light industrial construction industry and in particular facility maintenance; Must have Project infrastructure knowledge on building (Civil, Structural, Mechanical, Piping / Plumbing, Electrical &amp; Instrumentation); Ability to read &amp; analyze Architectural/MEP/Structural drawings is required 
 •  Familiar with Project management plan &amp; system in Mining Infrastructure activity; have working knowledge in Civil Infrastructure principles, design concepts &amp; operations, and awareness of operation regulatory; familiar with application of ISO 9001; has experience as Internal Auditor; be able to provide reporting; 
 •  Have Frontline level operational inspector certificate (POP) or qualifications certificate recognized by KaIT (Chief Mines Inspector) in accordance with level of position.. 
 •  Possess leadership traits and organizational, scheduling &amp; time management skills; Ability to work both independently and as a team player and thrive in a fast paced, high pressure environment dependent on managing multiple project timelines and schedules simultaneously; Ability to communicate well, and work productively with internal and external individuals; A commitment to safety and a desire to maintain our Indonesian mining operations to world class international safety standards; Demonstrate strong conceptual skills, and capable of developing lateral and practical solutions; High level of integrity and commitment; Good analytical, conflict resolution, sound decision making skills; 

 •  Excellent communication skills in English both verbal and written; computer literate. 

