Profile Middle East is a service provider with more than 20 years of experience in the market which specializes in Technical Field and HR Consultancy Services in the Industrial Sector (Oil &amp; Gas, Engineering, Construction, Commissioning) with our focus on the Middle East region and a worldwide presence. 

 We are currently selecting for <b>DESALINATION PACKAGES START UP LEADER</b>. 

<b> Ref code: CR_ 2306-100_</b> <b>Desalination Packages Start Up Leader</b> 

<b> Job summary </b> 

<b>MISSION:</b> 
 • Preparing commissioning progress reports to project management and commissioning department; 
 • Coordinating the assistance of the Vendor representatives; 
 • Supervising performance tests; 
 • Assisting the Project Manager in contacts with Client representatives for the handover of the package. 

<b>TASKS:</b> 
 • Reviewing Commissioning &amp; Start-up procedures; 
 • Coordinating Commissioning &amp; Start-up activities; 
 • Reviewing / analyzing the Commissioning &amp; Start-up planning received from Project Controls; 
 • Optimizing Commissioning &amp; Start-up activities being proactive in term of problem solving; 
 • Ensuring all spare parts are planned to be purchased by the project as per schedule; 
 • Reporting any deviation faced/observed and initiating corrective &amp; remedial actions; 
 • Ensuring that Commissioning &amp; Start-up teams are working in accordance with project codes and standards; 
 • Reviewing and approving Commissioning &amp; Start-up dossiers; 
 • Leading, organizing and executing all activities related to Desalination Package. 

<b>EDUCATION &amp; EXPERIENCE:</b> 
 • Bachelor’s degree in Mechanical Engineering; 
 • 20+ years of experience as Desalination Package Commissioning &amp; Start-up Leader and at least 5 projects. 

Proven commissioning experience on Thermal Desalination Packages “Vapour Mechanical Compressor” type designed with evaporator in vacum condition with the following main components: 
 • One fully assembled sea water pre-treatment facility skid. This skid includes a set of three hydrocyclone filters, with automatic valves and various instruments; 
 • Two evaporator skids mainly consisting of evaporation cell, vent condenser, plate heat exchangers, process pumps, backup heater, piping, instrumentation; 
 • Two vapour compressor skids, consisting of a chassis with assembled blower-motor and dedicated lube oil system; 
 • Chemical Dosing Skids. 

<b>Location:</b> Tangguh, Indonesia; 

<b> Contract duration: </b>1 month; 

<b> Starting date: </b>ASAP 

<b> Working schedule: </b>10 hours x 6 days. 

<b> Salary range: </b>N/A 

